<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="493" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,952,1555]" pageId="6" pageNumber="493">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1241,1267]" pageId="6" pageNumber="493">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Zwick, 1972:" authorityYear="1155" box="[324,562,1240,1267]" class="Insecta" family="Perlidae" genus="Anacroneuria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Plecoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="493" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="debilis">
<emphasis box="[324,562,1240,1267]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="493">Anacroneuria debilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was originally described by 
<bibRefCitation author="Pictet, F. J." box="[893,1040,1240,1267]" pageId="6" pageNumber="493" refId="ref9786" refString="Pictet, F. J. (1841) Histoire Naturelle Generale et Particuliere des Insectes Nevropteres. Famille des Perlides. J. Kessmann, Geneve, 423 pp. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 124172" type="book" year="1841">Pictet (1841)</bibRefCitation>
and the penial armature was illustrated by 
<bibRefCitation author="Zwick, P." box="[258,415,1276,1303]" pageId="6" pageNumber="493" pagination="1123 - 1194" refId="ref10509" refString="Zwick, P. (1972) Die Plecopteren Pictets und Burmeisters, mit Angaben uber weitere Arten (Insecta). Revue Suisse de Zoologie, 78, 1123 - 1194. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. part. 97087" type="journal article" year="1972">Zwick (1972)</bibRefCitation>
. In Central 
<collectingCountry box="[547,618,1276,1302]" name="Brazil" pageId="6" pageNumber="493">Brazil</collectingCountry>
, the species was recorded in the region of the Cidade de 
<collectingRegion box="[1261,1326,1276,1302]" country="Brazil" name="Goias" pageId="6" pageNumber="493">Goiás</collectingRegion>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Bispo, P. C. &amp; Costa, L. S. M. &amp; Novaes, M. C." pageId="6" pageNumber="493" pagination="591 - 596" refId="ref8412" refString="Bispo, P. C., Costa, L. S. M. &amp; Novaes, M. C. (2014) Two new species and a new record of Anacroneuria (Plecoptera: Perlidae) from Central Brazil. Zootaxa, 3779 (5), 591 - 596. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 3779.5.9" type="journal article" year="2014">
Bispo 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="493">et al</emphasis>
. 2014
</bibRefCitation>
), and in the present study we expanded the records for the Serra dos Pireneus, Chapada dos Veadeiros, and Emas National Park, 
<collectingRegion box="[395,524,1348,1375]" country="Brazil" name="Goias" pageId="6" pageNumber="493">Goiás state</collectingRegion>
. Recent studies revealed that this species has a large distribution and high morphological variation (
<bibRefCitation author="Bispo, P. C. &amp; Costa, L. S. M. &amp; Novaes, M. C." box="[394,595,1384,1411]" pageId="6" pageNumber="493" pagination="591 - 596" refId="ref8412" refString="Bispo, P. C., Costa, L. S. M. &amp; Novaes, M. C. (2014) Two new species and a new record of Anacroneuria (Plecoptera: Perlidae) from Central Brazil. Zootaxa, 3779 (5), 591 - 596. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 3779.5.9" type="journal article" year="2014">
Bispo 
<emphasis box="[469,520,1384,1410]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="493">et al</emphasis>
. 2014
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Novaes, M. C. &amp; Bispo, P. C." box="[607,876,1384,1411]" pageId="6" pageNumber="493" pagination="433 - 442" refId="ref9666" refString="Novaes, M. C. &amp; Bispo, P. C. (2014 c) Plecoptera from Minas Gerais State, southeastern Brazil. Zootaxa, 3856 (3), 433 - 442. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 3856.3.8" type="journal article" year="2014">Novaes &amp; Bispo 2014c</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Almeida, L. H. &amp; Duarte, T." box="[887,1168,1384,1411]" pageId="6" pageNumber="493" pagination="480 - 486" refId="ref7727" refString="Almeida, L. H. &amp; Duarte, T. (2017) A new species and records of Anacroneuria (Plecoptera: Perlidae) from the Ecological Station, Wenceslau Guimaraes, state of Bahia, Brazil. Zootaxa, 4247 (4), 480 - 486. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4247.4.9" type="journal article" year="2017">Almeida &amp; Duarte 2017</bibRefCitation>
). We also found a large variation in the penial armatures of the males of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Zwick, 1972:" authorityYear="1155" box="[695,801,1420,1447]" class="Insecta" family="Perlidae" genus="Anacroneuria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Plecoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="493" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="debilis">
<emphasis box="[695,801,1420,1447]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="493">A. debilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, especially in the keel and apex (
<figureCitation box="[1172,1242,1420,1447]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1940,1964]" captionTargetBox="[169,1410,189,1911]" captionTargetId="figure-19@5.[163,1425,181,1917]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 4. Comparison between adults of Anacroneuria debilis from Córrego Inferno (A–H), from Rio das Almas (I–L) and from Emas National Park (M–P). A, E, I, M: head and pronotum; B, F, J, N: penial armatures in lateral view; C, G, K, O: same, dorsal view; D, H, L, P: same, ventral view. Scale 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6816767" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6816767/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="493">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
). As indicated by previous studies (
<bibRefCitation author="Novaes, M. C. &amp; Bispo, P. C." box="[347,613,1456,1483]" pageId="6" pageNumber="493" pagination="433 - 442" refId="ref9666" refString="Novaes, M. C. &amp; Bispo, P. C. (2014 c) Plecoptera from Minas Gerais State, southeastern Brazil. Zootaxa, 3856 (3), 433 - 442. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 3856.3.8" type="journal article" year="2014">Novaes &amp; Bispo 2014c</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Almeida, L. H. &amp; Duarte, T." box="[623,897,1456,1483]" pageId="6" pageNumber="493" pagination="480 - 486" refId="ref7727" refString="Almeida, L. H. &amp; Duarte, T. (2017) A new species and records of Anacroneuria (Plecoptera: Perlidae) from the Ecological Station, Wenceslau Guimaraes, state of Bahia, Brazil. Zootaxa, 4247 (4), 480 - 486. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4247.4.9" type="journal article" year="2017">Almeida &amp; Duarte 2017</bibRefCitation>
) and our results, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Zwick, 1972:" authorityYear="1155" box="[1090,1197,1456,1483]" class="Insecta" family="Perlidae" genus="Anacroneuria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Plecoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="493" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="debilis">
<emphasis box="[1090,1197,1456,1483]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="493">A. debilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
may be composed of a group of cryptic species. Therefore, a more integrative study based on both morphological and molecular data is required for a better definition of this species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
